{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\" title=\"declaration uses 'sorry'\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/RigidBody/SolidSphere.html#RigidBody.solidSphere_inertiaTensor\"><span class=\"name\">RigidBody</span>.<span class=\"name\">solidSphere_inertiaTensor</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m </span><span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/NNReal/Defs.html#NNReal\">NNReal</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hr</span> : <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/RigidBody/SolidSphere.html#RigidBody.solidSphere\">solidSphere</a> <span class=\"fn\">3</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">R</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/RigidBody/Basic.html#RigidBody.inertiaTensor\">inertiaTensor</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> (<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">2</span> / <span class=\"fn\">5</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">m</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">R</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">2</span>) <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The moment of inertia tensor of a solid sphere through its center of mass is\n`2/5 m R^2 * I`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/ClassicalMechanics/RigidBody/SolidSphere.html#RigidBody.solidSphere_inertiaTensor","kind":"theorem","line":70,"name":"RigidBody.solidSphere_inertiaTensor","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean